{{DISPLAYTITLE:''Down Girl: The Logic of Misogyny''}} {{Infobox book | name = Down Girl: The Logic of Misogyny | author = [[Kate Manne]] | subject = [[analytic feminism]] | published = 2017 ([[Oxford University Press]])<ref name=global/> | pages = | isbn = 9780190604981 | italic title=no }}
'''''Down Girl: The Logic of Misogyny''''' is a book by [[Kate Manne]], treating [[misogyny]] in tradition of analytic feminist philosophy.<ref name=global>Manne, Kate [https://global.oup.com/academic/product/down-girl-9780190604981?q=down%20girl&lang=en&cc=us "Down Girl: The Logic of Misogyny"], Published 8 November 2017 by Oxford University Press, {{ISBN|9780190604981}}, Retrieved on 12 November 2018.</ref>
Manne proposes that [[patriarchy]], [[sexism]], and misogyny are distinct: sexism is an ideology justifying patriarchy, while misogyny enforces patriarchy by punishing women who deviate from patriarchy.<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/books/2017/dec/20/down-girl-kate-manne-review "Guardian Review"], Retrieved on 12 November 2018.</ref> Manne believes dehumanization of women is not necessary for misogynist violence.<ref>[https://kiej.georgetown.edu/kate-manne-girl-logic-misogyny-oxford-university-press-2017/ "Book Review by Kennedy Institute of Ethics Journal"], Retrieved on 12 November 2018.</ref>
